	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A 23-year-old man's body was discovered in an open field after he was stabbed to death in Mitchells Plain, Cape Town, on Monday. Police responded to a complaint about the discovery of the body near Durban Road, Portlands, at 11:45. "The deceased had been stabbed in the chest with an unknown sharp object," police spokesperson Captain FC van Wyk said. "No persons have been arrested. Police are investigating a murder." Anyone with information about the incident is asked to contact the investigating officer Detective Sergeant Errol Bedford of Mitchells Plain serious and violent crimes unit at 082 777 8076.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  